From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 15:02:00 +0800
Subject: Remove HeadlessChrome User-Agent leak

Under PureCloak, prevent the "Headless" prefix from being prepended to
the User-Agent string when running in headless mode. This prevents the
HeadlessChrome/browser fingerprint from leaking via the UA string,
which is a common anti-bot detection signal.

The change is guarded by BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK) to ensure the existing
behavior is preserved for non-PureCloak builds.

---
 components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc b/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc
index 608bea5cb3..6973151e4d 100644
--- a/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc
+++ b/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc
@@ -215,9 +215,11 @@ const blink::UserAgentBrandList GetUserAgentBrandFullVersionListInternal(
 // depending on the Reduce User-Agent reduction phase features.
 std::string GetUserAgentInternal() {
   std::string product = GetProductAndVersion();
+#if !BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
   if (base::CommandLine::ForCurrentProcess()->HasSwitch(kHeadless)) {
     product.insert(0, "Headless");
   }
+#endif
 
 #if BUILDFLAG(IS_ANDROID) || BUILDFLAG(IS_IOS)
   if (base::CommandLine::ForCurrentProcess()->HasSwitch(kUseMobileUserAgent)) {
